2. Hard Acceptance Gates (Pre-Production Requirements)


Production is blocked unless all gates pass.


G1 – SAF Durability Gate (Android)


Requirement: Persistent read/write access to removable USB/SD across reboot.


Implementation Steps


1. Use ACTION_OPEN_DOCUMENT_TREE




2. Capture returned Uri




3. Call:


contentResolver.takePersistableUriPermission(
    uri,
    Intent.FLAG_GRANT_READ_URI_PERMISSION |
    Intent.FLAG_GRANT_WRITE_URI_PERMISSION
);




4. Store URI string encrypted in:


EncryptedSharedPreferences


Backed by Android Keystore






5. On cold start:


Rehydrate URI


Rebuild tree via DocumentFile.fromTreeUri()








Validation


Write file


Reboot device


Modify file


Delete file


No re-prompt allowed




If force-stopped → permission recovery logic must run in MainActivity.onCreate().




---


G2 – Offline Inference Gate


Requirement: llama.cpp loads GGUF via mmap and generates tokens offline.


Build Requirements


NDK compiled with:


-O2


USE_OPENMP=1


16KB page alignment (Android 15+)




No ART heap model loading


Must use mmap on file descriptor




Pass Criteria


Sustained 10-minute generation


No OOM killer


No thermal crash


Stable token throughput






---


G3 – Atomic Update Gate


Requirement: DB Pack swap without corruption under power loss.


Required


SQLite WAL mode


fsync enforcement


SHA-256 verification


Atomic rename swap




Must survive:


USB removal mid-copy


Power loss mid-swap






